{
  "style": "APA",
  "texts": [
    "\"CM\" indicates Construction Methods, where \"HG\" indicates Human Generated Corpora, \"MC\" indicates Model Constructed Corpora, and \"CI\" indicates Collection and Improvement of Existing Corpora filtering and deduplication processes on Common Crawl.",
    "It ultimately retains highquality English text totaling 5T tokens.",
    "C4 (Raffel et al, 2020), derived from Common Crawl crawler data from April 2019, undergoes processing with multiple filters, removing useless, harmful, and non-English text.",
    "In contrast to C4, mC4 (Xue et al, 2021), CC100 (Conneau et al, 2020), OSCAR 22.01 (Abadji et al, 2022), and RedPajama-V2 (Together, 2023) retain multilingual data during the cleaning process, utilizing different cleaning pipelines.",
    "CC-Stories (Trinh and Le, 2018) and RealNews (Zellers et al, 2019b) are selected subsets of text content from Common Crawl based on specific themes."
  ],
